olive oil
1 packet Beef Rump
1 tin sweetcorn
1 cucumber
1 tomato
1 bag baby spinach leaves
½ lemon
1 packet Mild Chipotle Sauce
1 bag slaw mix
1 packet Corn Chips
1 bag herbs
1 packet garlic aioli
1 sachet Tex-Mex spice blend

• Place beef between two sheets of
baking paper. Pound with rolling pin
until slightly flattened (this ensures
it’s extra tender!)
• In a bowl, combine beef and spice
blend with a drizzle of olive oil.
Season
• Heat oil in a frying pan over high heat
• Cook beef, turning, for 5-6 mins or
until cooked to your liking
• Transfer to a plate to rest

• Drain the corn
• Roughly chop cucumber, tomato
and spinach. Slice the lemon
• Combine chipotle sauce and garlic
aioli
• In a bowl, combine corn, cucumber,
tomato, spinach, slaw mix, 1/2 the
chipotle aioli, a squeeze of lemon
juice and a drizzle of olive oil.
Season

• Slice the steak
• Plate up slaw and steak
• Serve with corn chips, torn herbs,
remaining chipotle aioli and lemon
wedges. Enjoy!